HEADWORD: Marbrinus
<hw>Mar*bri"nus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL., fr. OF.
& F. <ets>marble</ets> marble. See <er>Marble</er>.]</ety> <def>A cloth
woven so as to imitate the appearance of marble; -- much used in the
15th and 16th centuries.</def> <rj><au>Beck (Draper's
Dict.).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

